{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcwaH2C942im5dyiqWk5N","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TPz1y2WKnQDs6nKfvphQk7","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2-rundirs-594d5c68-with-lessons-ledger--ll2-r2/memory/ci-fixture-race-condition.md","content":"---\nname: ci-fixture-race-condition\ndescription: Intermittent CI test failures were caused by a race in fixture setup over a shared file\nmetadata:\n  type: project\n---\n\nAn intermittent CI test failure was traced to a race condition in fixture setup: multiple tests touched a shared file concurrently. Fixed by adding a lock around the shared-file access in the fixture.\n\n**Why:** The failure was intermittent and CI-only, so it looked like flakiness rather than a real bug — it took an afternoon to pin down that fixture setup, not the test logic, was racing on a shared file.\n\n**How to apply:** When a test fails only intermittently (especially under parallel CI), suspect shared mutable state in fixture/setup code before the test body. Guard shared-file (or other shared-resource) access in fixtures with a lock.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":696,"cache_read_input_tokens":20504,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":696},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"57e7beaa-4a0a-4ac1-be92-a6808ea451e3","uuid":"952d2223-9c61-4e56-969a-5a02a6f30c89","request_id":"req_011CcwaH1Dr5xbVHXxAPfEDv"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TPz1y2WKnQDs6nKfvphQk7","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2-rundirs-594d5c68-with-lessons-ledger--ll2-r2/memory/ci-fixture-race-condition.md (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"57e7beaa-4a0a-4ac1-be92-a6808ea451e3","uuid":"cbca3a47-0301-4fbc-b93e-2ee478124e11","timestamp":"2026-07-12T05:00:37.852Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2-rundirs-594d5c68-with-lessons-ledger--ll2-r2/memory/ci-fixture-race-condition.md","content":"---\nname: ci-fixture-race-condition\ndescription: Intermittent CI test failures were caused by a race in fixture setup over a shared file\nmetadata: \n  node_type: memory\n  type: project\n  originSessionId: 57e7beaa-4a0a-4ac1-be92-a6808ea451e3\n---\n\nAn intermittent CI test failure was traced to a race condition in fixture setup: multiple tests touched a shared file concurrently. Fixed by adding a lock around the shared-file access in the fixture.\n\n**Why:** The failure was intermittent and CI-only, so it looked like flakiness rather than a real bug — it took an afternoon to pin down that fixture setup, not the test logic, was racing on a shared file.\n\n**How to apply:** When a test fails only intermittently (especially under parallel CI), suspect shared mutable state in fixture/setup code before the test body. Guard shared-file (or other shared-resource) access in fixtures with a lock.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
